1
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:25,620
What does it mean to truly disappear?

2
00:00:36,820 --> 00:00:37,880
You asked for this.

3
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:40,180
Is this enough?

4
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:25,440
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

5
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:49,220
He!

6
00:01:49,990 --> 00:01:51,090
He!

7
00:01:51,690 --> 00:01:52,990
Haowei drowned!

8
00:01:53,450 --> 00:01:55,259
He was sent to the main island hospital!

9
00:01:55,259 --> 00:01:56,490
Are you being chased by a dog?

10
00:01:56,490 --> 00:01:57,229
What happened?

11
00:01:57,229 --> 00:01:58,900
Haowei drowned
and was sent to the main island hospital!

12
00:01:58,900 --> 00:01:59,360
Sent to...

13
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,770
ID card and...

14
00:02:00,770 --> 00:02:01,530
emergency contact.

15
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:01,970
His luggage is here!

16
00:02:01,970 --> 00:02:03,770
-His luggage is here!
-Hurry up!

17
00:02:13,140 --> 00:02:13,750
Miss,

18
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:14,710
a ticket for the next boat,

19
00:02:14,710 --> 00:02:15,210
please.

20
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:15,680
-Please be quick.
-I'm sorry.

21
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,180
Because of the big storm,

22
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:18,720
our boat has left.

23
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,820
No more boats today.

24
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:20,690
No more boats?

25
00:02:20,690 --> 00:02:21,420
No.

26
00:02:21,650 --> 00:02:22,050
Wait...

27
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:23,320
Miss, I have something urgent, please...

28
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:25,050
Please, I'm begging you, miss!

29
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:32,680
I'll go first.

30
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,100
I'll play a five‑card straight.

31
00:02:34,100 --> 00:02:34,770
Here.

32
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:36,300
Three, four, five, six, seven.

33
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:37,170
A straight.

34
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:38,670
You want me to play, right?

35
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:39,400
Pass.

36
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:41,110
Can you play?

37
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:41,710
No. Pass.

38
00:02:41,710 --> 00:02:42,810
Zhong,

39
00:02:42,810 --> 00:02:43,370
Could you please

40
00:02:43,370 --> 00:02:44,310
take me to the main island?

41
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:44,840
Please,

42
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,310
I'm begging you!

43
00:02:45,310 --> 00:02:46,480
I have something urgent!

44
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,350
I can't.

45
00:02:48,050 --> 00:02:49,280
Young man, listen,

46
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,480
there's a big storm today.

47
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:51,750
Wait, Zhong, listen,

48
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:52,579
my friend drowned.

49
00:02:52,579 --> 00:02:53,380
He's on the main island
for emergency treatment.

50
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:54,150
I need to be there!

51
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:54,920
Let's go!

52
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:55,720
Listen,

53
00:02:55,790 --> 00:02:57,460
they told all of us to come back.

54
00:02:57,460 --> 00:02:59,020
The storm is too heavy, okay?

55
00:02:59,020 --> 00:03:00,430
Calm down. You can ask Da.

56
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:01,560
Conditions out at sea are really rough.

57
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,390
It's dangerous. Don't go out.

58
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,960
Please take me there!

59
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,630
I'm begging you!

60
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:06,600
I'll pay you as much as you want.

61
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:08,830
It's not that I don't want to.
I just can't.

62
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:10,940
It's too dangerous.

63
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:13,070
Alright.

64
00:03:14,140 --> 00:03:14,940
There's nothing we can do.

65
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:15,870
Don't worry.

66
00:03:16,410 --> 00:03:17,110
Everything will be fine.

67
00:03:17,110 --> 00:03:18,140
It'll be alright.

68
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,160
Excuse me!

69
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:30,990
Excuse me!

70
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:32,290
Make way, please!

71
00:03:32,290 --> 00:03:33,590
Excuse me!

72
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,020
Drowned, OHCA.

73
00:03:41,570 --> 00:03:44,640
One, two, three, four, five,

74
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:47,570
six, seven, eight, nine, ten...

75
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,480
So,

76
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,400
whether it's He Xiangyong

77
00:03:53,510 --> 00:03:54,970
or Zhong Xiaoyou,

78
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:58,240
I'm always that useless stone.

79
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:01,220
I'll only hurt people around me.

80
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:03,920
I can't protect the people I love.

81
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:09,360
Hong!

82
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:10,860
I'm begging you!

83
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:11,930
Please help me!

84
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:12,900
I don't want anything.

85
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,830
I only hope Chen Haowei
can come back safely.

86
00:04:14,830 --> 00:04:16,029
He's in danger on the main island.

87
00:04:16,029 --> 00:04:17,500
Could you please save him?

88
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,200
You can help me,

89
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,070
right?

90
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,970
Xiangyong, calm down.

91
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:22,170
Calm down.

92
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:24,310
Have a candy first.

93
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:29,110
Your favorite watermelon candy.

94
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:34,620
Don't you want it?

95
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:37,990
There's no turning back.

96
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:38,960
I've told you

97
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:41,360
I have no right
to help you change anything.

98
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:45,020
You have to bear all the consequences
of your wish, good or bad.

99
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,300
This is the path you must walk

100
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:50,000
once your wish comes true.

101
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:05,420
I made a wish, and I can pay the price.

102
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,370
But what about Chen Haowei?

103
00:05:08,290 --> 00:05:09,320
He didn't even make a wish.

104
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,860
Why does he have to bear the consequences
of the mistake I made?

105
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:13,730
I can't let him die for nothing.

106
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,010
You can't just watch him die!

107
00:05:23,090 --> 00:05:24,350
Instead of blaming me,

108
00:05:24,610 --> 00:05:26,510
you should reflect on yourself.

109
00:05:27,030 --> 00:05:28,630
Who started all this?

110
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,140
And who was it that grew unsatisfied
with the wish

111
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:32,409
and foolishly tried to change it?

112
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,250
Did I force

113
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,810
Chen Haowei to pick up the stone?

114
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:37,310
I didn't mean it!

115
00:05:39,250 --> 00:05:40,180
When I saw the shooting star,

116
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:42,240
I wasn't serious about making a wish!

117
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,570
How could you
take my casual words seriously?

118
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:48,450
It's so unfair for a wish to come true.

119
00:05:50,930 --> 00:05:51,880
Your subconscious

120
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,610
has led your life to this point.

121
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:56,060
Now you're just blaming it on fate.

122
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:00,830
You said you didn't mean it.

123
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:03,210
But if you'd never thought about it,

124
00:06:03,210 --> 00:06:05,140
why would you have said it out loud?

125
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,280
Just admit it.

126
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:08,510
You wanted to abandon
your identity as He Xiangyong,

127
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,270
didn't you?

128
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:11,220
Can you say that you've been
completely unwilling to accept

129
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:13,950
the new identity as Zhong Xiaoyou
the whole time?

130
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,500
So,

131
00:06:28,130 --> 00:06:30,000
I can only accept it.

132
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:33,770
I can't save myself.

133
00:06:35,370 --> 00:06:36,700
I even hurt Chen Haowei,

134
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:40,370
but there's nothing I can do to fix it.

135
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:44,780
Where there is gain, there is loss—

136
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:47,440
that's the rule of this world.

137
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,360
Every choice has a price.

138
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:52,030
No one can get away.

139
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,030
Why are you laughing?

140
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,380
Now I get it.

141
00:07:18,380 --> 00:07:20,550
I started all this,

142
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,960
so let me end it.

143
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,820
I made a wish,

144
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:30,730
and I'll bear the consequences.

145
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:31,460
Xiangyong!

146
00:07:58,090 --> 00:07:59,290
Why don't you go home?

147
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,380
Why are you sitting here?

148
00:08:03,490 --> 00:08:05,200
I just saw Xiaoyou at the dock.

149
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,700
What happened to him?

150
00:08:08,130 --> 00:08:09,070
Are you okay?

151
00:08:12,990 --> 00:08:14,430
Chen Haowei drowned.

152
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,040
I heard he's still unconscious.

153
00:08:20,410 --> 00:08:20,950
I really don't know

154
00:08:20,950 --> 00:08:22,550
how this could happen.

155
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:24,450
Is it because of the wish?

156
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,380
So, did he drown today

157
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:27,790
because of the wish?

158
00:08:31,860 --> 00:08:33,289
I'm really scared.

159
00:08:33,830 --> 00:08:35,289
Will the wish backfire,

160
00:08:35,289 --> 00:08:36,760
like Xiaoyou said before?

161
00:08:37,059 --> 00:08:38,600
Something happened to Chen Haowei today.

162
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,330
So, would it be you and me next time?

163
00:08:40,330 --> 00:08:40,929
I...

164
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,400
Don't overthink it.

165
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,169
I'll be fine.

166
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:45,770
We'll be alright.

167
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:48,490
I don't know.

168
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:50,270
I always thought

169
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:51,840
we only needed love.

170
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:54,050
But if the wish

171
00:08:54,050 --> 00:08:55,850
is meant to bring us misfortune,

172
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,250
then I don't want anything.

173
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:05,680
I can't let anything happen to you.

174
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,140
I won't allow it.

175
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,600
Don't be afraid.

176
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:15,660
I'll be here.

177
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,610
Who are you?

178
00:09:57,880 --> 00:09:58,940
It doesn't matter.

179
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:00,740
Do you want to know where this is?

180
00:10:06,620 --> 00:10:07,820
Where are you going?

181
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:09,620
Please let me introduce.

182
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:32,110
You've been running for a long time.

183
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:33,510
Aren't you tired?

184
00:10:37,130 --> 00:10:38,110
You're tired.

185
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:44,420
Let me introduce.

186
00:10:44,420 --> 00:10:46,260
Here is your time.

187
00:10:46,690 --> 00:10:48,360
Here are your years.

188
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:49,960
And this is

189
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:52,360
everything you've ever been through.

190
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:54,900
What do you think?

191
00:10:55,730 --> 00:10:56,990
Isn't it spectacular?

192
00:11:03,610 --> 00:11:05,940
Give me some reaction!

193
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:07,800
It took me a long time to make this!

194
00:11:10,210 --> 00:11:12,600
So, are you really going to
exchange He Xiangyong

195
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,890
for Chen Haowei?

196
00:11:17,380 --> 00:11:18,780
Can you make that happen?

197
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:24,470
It doesn't matter if I can do it or not.

198
00:11:25,450 --> 00:11:27,150
I really admire your courage.

199
00:11:28,570 --> 00:11:29,600
But I think...

200
00:11:29,930 --> 00:11:31,570
with that courage,

201
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:33,370
you should face

202
00:11:33,370 --> 00:11:35,470
your past wounds.

203
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:39,710
Look, every life in this universe

204
00:11:39,710 --> 00:11:41,010
has its value.

205
00:11:41,710 --> 00:11:43,970
Your life matters, and so do other lives.

206
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:48,680
Are you listening to me or not?

207
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,210
Let's go take a look.

208
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:31,360
Are you using him as a scapegoat

209
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,900
just because he's young?

210
00:12:34,230 --> 00:12:36,330
Don't use the law to threaten me.

211
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:42,230
He Xiangyong said
he would take responsibility.

212
00:12:43,410 --> 00:12:45,740
So we will take responsibility to the end.

213
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,830
Let's go.

214
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:52,850
What?

215
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,480
Let's go. Where are we going?

216
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:56,920
Hey,

217
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:58,780
where are you going during class?

218
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:02,860
The instructor is here.

219
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:03,830
The instructor is here, up there.

220
00:13:03,830 --> 00:13:04,560
-What's going on?
-Let's go!

221
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:05,620
What are you doing?

222
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:45,800
I want to borrow it.

223
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:46,940
I...

224
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:48,110
I think...

225
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:49,740
Please lend it to me.

226
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:51,340
I'll give you back next week.

227
00:13:52,370 --> 00:13:53,940
Aren't you in the art class?

228
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:55,770
You can draw it yourself, right?

229
00:14:01,630 --> 00:14:03,330
Class is starting. I gotta go.

230
00:14:08,770 --> 00:14:09,870
Auntie.

231
00:14:13,050 --> 00:14:14,050
Are you okay?

232
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:16,090
Why did you get into a fight?

233
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:18,440
Are you hurt?

234
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:21,040
I'm fine.

235
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:26,840
Actually, I don't know
what's wrong with me.

236
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,340
But I think

237
00:14:31,380 --> 00:14:32,680
I hurt

238
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:34,460
a very good friend.

239
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,890
It's not scary to be forgotten.

240
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:43,990
What's really scary is that

241
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:45,930
you don't know you were loved.

242
00:14:48,730 --> 00:14:50,930
Time in the universe is always passing.

243
00:14:51,870 --> 00:14:53,870
Are you sure you want to trap

244
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,070
He Xiangyong here forever?

245
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,560
Then what should I do now?

246
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:12,590
You've never given up.

247
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:14,470
I knew it.

248
00:15:38,780 --> 00:15:39,650
Thank you, sir.

249
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:41,040
But I don't want it.

250
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:45,980
This is your favorite seaweed flavor.

251
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:48,890
Don't want it? Fine.

252
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:52,350
What kind of god
would slack off like this?

253
00:15:57,700 --> 00:16:01,400
Because I have a capable beast.

254
00:16:16,950 --> 00:16:18,090
Why did you do that?

255
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:22,430
Because you let it slip,

256
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:25,370
telling him something about gain and loss.

257
00:16:26,430 --> 00:16:28,030
How would I know he'd do that?

258
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:30,020
You're the one who set the rules.

259
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:36,590
Humans are so special.

260
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:39,080
With all the past,

261
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:40,840
pain, and love,

262
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,900
they move on
and face the rest of their lives.

263
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:46,650
That way, shooting stars

264
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:49,110
will help them find
where they truly belong.

265
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:54,860
He Xiangyong has learned

266
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:57,120
the correct way to watch shooting stars.

267
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:58,790
Here.

268
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:02,610
It's time to return it.

269
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,349
Well,

270
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:22,410
any dough twists left?

271
00:17:26,790 --> 00:17:27,569
No.

272
00:17:39,670 --> 00:17:40,300
Excuse me,

273
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:41,120
where is Chen Haowei?

274
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,020
Chen Haowei...

275
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:42,910
Bed 9.

276
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:43,410
Over there.

277
00:17:43,410 --> 00:17:44,340
Bed 9?

278
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,290
How could I...

279
00:18:52,850 --> 00:18:53,930
forget you?

280
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:00,430
He Xiangyong...

281
00:19:04,690 --> 00:19:05,920
He Xiangyong...

282
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,560
I'm back.

283
00:19:24,630 --> 00:19:25,830
I'm sorry...

284
00:19:31,530 --> 00:19:32,970
I'm sorry!

285
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:44,480
Why did you suddenly come out?

286
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:47,450
What are you looking at?

287
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:49,860
It seems

288
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:51,790
my wish has disappeared.

289
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,530
What wish?

290
00:20:57,570 --> 00:20:59,170
I remember He Xiangyong now.

291
00:21:00,340 --> 00:21:02,340
Do you remember him?

292
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,580
Isn't he your friend?

293
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:06,980
I sleep next to you,

294
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:09,210
but you're thinking about another person.

295
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:10,340
That's weird.

296
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,650
No, that's not what I meant.

297
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:14,870
Well,

298
00:21:15,820 --> 00:21:17,090
do you still like me?

299
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:19,190
Idiot.

300
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,250
What are you talking about?

301
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:26,160
It's okay.

302
00:21:26,730 --> 00:21:27,460
Anyway,

303
00:21:27,830 --> 00:21:28,600
confessions

304
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:30,600
get easier with practice, you know?

305
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:32,350
My mom always says,

306
00:21:32,770 --> 00:21:34,700
"You should take the initiative."

307
00:21:34,970 --> 00:21:36,700
Even if you forget it 100 times,

308
00:21:36,910 --> 00:21:39,240
I'll confess my feelings to you 100 times.

309
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:44,990
That's enough.

310
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,240
I know.

311
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:50,950
What..

312
00:21:50,950 --> 00:21:52,020
do you know?

313
00:21:52,850 --> 00:21:53,980
I know you like me.

314
00:21:56,090 --> 00:21:57,260
You remember now?

315
00:21:57,830 --> 00:21:59,430
Many times.

316
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:00,990
What else do you remember?

317
00:22:00,990 --> 00:22:02,530
Do you remember...

318
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:13,720
One more time.

319
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:15,720
One more time?

320
00:22:30,490 --> 00:22:32,760
So, you went to this strange space.

321
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:33,930
You kept running,

322
00:22:33,930 --> 00:22:35,070
but you always ended up in the same place.

323
00:22:35,070 --> 00:22:36,080
Then you met

324
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:37,370
a weird man

325
00:22:37,370 --> 00:22:38,540
in a pink coat.

326
00:22:46,180 --> 00:22:47,310
Turns out

327
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:48,780
you gave up your own life,

328
00:22:48,780 --> 00:22:50,510
yet you saved the day in the end.

329
00:22:50,610 --> 00:22:51,480
But

330
00:22:51,810 --> 00:22:54,210
it seems everyone has different memories.

331
00:22:54,220 --> 00:22:55,950
Have you talked to Chen Haowei?

332
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:58,790
It doesn't matter.

333
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:03,950
But I still remember

334
00:23:04,330 --> 00:23:05,660
someone said

335
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:07,570
I was worthless

336
00:23:07,620 --> 00:23:08,960
and beat me up.

337
00:23:09,570 --> 00:23:11,170
You hold grudges, don't you?

338
00:23:11,370 --> 00:23:12,400
I didn't know

339
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:13,570
you were He Xiangyong.

340
00:23:13,570 --> 00:23:15,770
That's why I got so angry and pushed you.

341
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:17,470
Besides, you knew I was Li Wanzhe,

342
00:23:17,470 --> 00:23:19,080
yet you called me a coward.

343
00:23:20,340 --> 00:23:21,750
You're the one who holds grudges.

344
00:23:21,750 --> 00:23:23,150
You like to hold grudges.

345
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:29,550
Anyway,

346
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:31,280
after going through this,

347
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:32,710
I've finally realized

348
00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:35,140
I was always

349
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:38,090
seeking approval from people
that were not worth it,

350
00:23:38,370 --> 00:23:40,070
trying to prove something,

351
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:42,230
only to fail again and again

352
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:46,130
and push the people who loved me
further and further away.

353
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:48,530
So now,

354
00:23:48,810 --> 00:23:51,140
I only want to live in the moment,

355
00:23:51,540 --> 00:23:52,610
enjoy my life,

356
00:23:53,060 --> 00:23:54,920
and cherish the people around me,

357
00:23:55,370 --> 00:23:57,700
so that I won't
let the shooting star down.

358
00:23:59,450 --> 00:24:00,780
What a touching speech.

359
00:24:01,030 --> 00:24:02,890
He Xiangyong has really changed.

360
00:24:06,020 --> 00:24:08,290
I guess we won't see each other often.

361
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:10,520
Why?

362
00:24:10,790 --> 00:24:11,990
Because I'm staying.

363
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:14,530
Listen,

364
00:24:14,970 --> 00:24:16,630
I made an important decision.

365
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:17,840
What decision?

366
00:24:21,630 --> 00:24:24,230
I'm going to travel the world with Soukai!

367
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:28,250
Are you going to be a crew member?

368
00:24:28,250 --> 00:24:29,380
No.

369
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:31,810
I'm going to be Soukai's navigator.

370
00:24:32,320 --> 00:24:35,050
I want to go to
the edges of the world with him.

371
00:24:35,690 --> 00:24:37,650
If he's a ship, I'll be the helm.

372
00:24:38,020 --> 00:24:40,280
We'll sail to the great course together.

373
00:24:49,770 --> 00:24:51,430
"Maritime Applied English,"

374
00:24:52,290 --> 00:24:54,690
"Ship Fire Prevention and Safety,"

375
00:24:54,970 --> 00:24:56,910
and "Marine Meteorology."

376
00:24:57,340 --> 00:24:59,610
Does this teach literature?

377
00:24:59,930 --> 00:25:01,230
Shut up!

378
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:03,960
I have a strong literary background.

379
00:25:07,620 --> 00:25:08,950
But didn't you say

380
00:25:09,620 --> 00:25:11,250
you only wanted

381
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:12,850
a short-term relationship?

382
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:17,230
But now, I want a relationship with Soukai

383
00:25:17,230 --> 00:25:18,760
that never ends.

384
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,260
I know the result

385
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:24,090
might be different from what I expected.

386
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:25,800
But I still want to be brave

387
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,400
and love with all my heart this time.

388
00:25:28,810 --> 00:25:30,610
You're absolutely insane.

389
00:25:31,210 --> 00:25:32,480
Don't say that.

390
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:34,540
Maybe he happens to love my insanity.

391
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:42,080
He Xiangyong is great!

392
00:25:45,420 --> 00:25:46,810
Li Wanzhe is also great!

393
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:50,680
Li Wanzhe is not a coward!

394
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:55,300
He Xiangyong has great value!

395
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:59,300
He Xiangyong is a crybaby!

396
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:03,170
Li Wanzhe never takes a shower!

397
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:06,170
Li Wanzhe takes a shower every two days!

398
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,530
So disgusting!

399
00:26:39,270 --> 00:26:40,070
Come here.

400
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:43,150
Watch your head.

401
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,200
It's so small.

402
00:26:46,180 --> 00:26:47,920
This is the left and right wheel.

403
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:49,050
Can I touch it?

404
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:50,150
Sure, go ahead.

405
00:26:57,530 --> 00:26:59,130
It should be like this.

406
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:00,260
Come on.

407
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:01,830
Okay.

408
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:05,070
What affects maritime visibility?

409
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:07,040
What affects visibility...

410
00:27:07,530 --> 00:27:09,460
I remember there are five factors.

411
00:27:09,510 --> 00:27:10,610
Rain,

412
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:12,480
fog, cliffs,

413
00:27:13,210 --> 00:27:15,380
rock...

414
00:27:16,650 --> 00:27:18,320
rock particles, and dust.

415
00:27:19,350 --> 00:27:19,980
No.

416
00:27:20,010 --> 00:27:20,780
No?

417
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:25,680
Try to list the factors
that reduce air temperature.

418
00:27:25,990 --> 00:27:27,320
I know. Three factors.

419
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:31,180
Contact cooling, radiative cooling,
and adiabatic cooling.

420
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:33,550
-Yes!
-Yes!

421
00:27:37,210 --> 00:27:39,010
Chen Haowei, can you do it or not?

422
00:27:39,540 --> 00:27:40,740
Okay, no problem.

423
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:45,940
It's clean.

424
00:27:45,940 --> 00:27:46,440
Of course,

425
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,040
I'm also good at cooking now.

426
00:27:52,730 --> 00:27:54,430
Do I have any reward?

427
00:27:57,450 --> 00:27:58,790
What reward do you want?

428
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,670
Chen Haowei...

429
00:28:17,690 --> 00:28:18,790
Fire...

430
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,440
You feel it?

431
00:28:24,150 --> 00:28:24,910
No!

432
00:28:24,910 --> 00:28:26,320
The fire of the gas stove!

433
00:28:26,620 --> 00:28:27,620
Gas stove?

434
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,400
You can put the shrimp in.

435
00:28:35,070 --> 00:28:36,110
Give it to me.

436
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:55,830
Go.

437
00:28:56,460 --> 00:28:57,050
Like this?

438
00:28:57,050 --> 00:28:57,580
Yes.

439
00:28:58,140 --> 00:28:58,680
Yes.

440
00:28:59,020 --> 00:29:00,180
-Chen Haowei.
-You can swim now.

441
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:01,180
I can swim now.

442
00:29:01,180 --> 00:29:02,220
Soukai is great.

443
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:02,920
He's good at this.

444
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:04,120
He used to be a sailor.

445
00:29:04,390 --> 00:29:05,120
I can swim now.

446
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:05,890
Yes, you can.

447
00:29:05,890 --> 00:29:06,790
-Chen Haowei.
-You can swim now.

448
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:07,860
I can swim now.

449
00:29:07,860 --> 00:29:08,360
Yes.

450
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:09,790
Xiangyong, don't swim too far.

451
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:10,850
Come back a little.

452
00:32:15,540 --> 00:32:16,810
Want to steal food?

453
00:32:18,100 --> 00:32:19,570
Part-timer.

454
00:32:22,460 --> 00:32:24,460
Just tasting the dishes for my boss.

455
00:32:24,890 --> 00:32:25,930
No need.

456
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,250
I've tasted every dish.

457
00:32:27,250 --> 00:32:28,450
They're really good.

458
00:32:30,390 --> 00:32:32,390
Then I want to taste something else.

459
00:32:32,390 --> 00:32:33,290
What?

460
00:32:39,740 --> 00:32:40,700
So beautiful.

461
00:32:44,610 --> 00:32:45,820
Congratulations!

462
00:32:46,690 --> 00:32:48,410
-Dad, let's eat.
-Uncle Hua, let's eat.

463
00:32:48,410 --> 00:32:49,540
Let's eat.

464
00:32:49,780 --> 00:32:50,750
Let's eat.

465
00:32:51,450 --> 00:32:53,120
It looks amazing.

466
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,140
Dudu, let's eat.

467
00:32:56,350 --> 00:32:57,120
Time to eat.

468
00:32:57,120 --> 00:32:58,190
Thanks.

469
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,260
The sausage...

470
00:33:02,950 --> 00:33:04,820
I think it's from Xiaoyou.

471
00:33:05,390 --> 00:33:06,960
Really? Let me try.

472
00:33:09,570 --> 00:33:11,030
Is it really from Xiaoyou?

473
00:33:17,930 --> 00:33:19,500
Yes, it must be him.

474
00:33:23,300 --> 00:33:24,170
It's good.

475
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:28,550
I wonder

476
00:33:29,390 --> 00:33:30,820
if his relationship with his father

477
00:33:30,820 --> 00:33:32,220
has gotten any better.

478
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:38,030
Why do you care so much about
other people's son?

479
00:33:38,030 --> 00:33:39,060
Your son cooked this meal.

480
00:33:39,060 --> 00:33:40,520
Shouldn't you praise him?

481
00:33:41,030 --> 00:33:41,860
Yes, Mr. He.

482
00:33:42,170 --> 00:33:43,650
Xiangyong made all of these.

483
00:33:43,650 --> 00:33:44,770
They're good, right?

484
00:33:44,770 --> 00:33:45,570
Yes.

485
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:47,000
Look, these are all your favorites.

486
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,440
I know. I have eyes.

487
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:50,210
I don't need you to tell me.

488
00:33:52,380 --> 00:33:53,150
Alright.

489
00:33:53,970 --> 00:33:55,260
I just wanted to remind you

490
00:33:55,260 --> 00:33:57,990
that besides eating and speaking,

491
00:33:58,370 --> 00:34:00,540
your mouth can also express feelings,

492
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:01,660
you know?

493
00:34:06,490 --> 00:34:07,260
Dad.

494
00:34:09,150 --> 00:34:11,750
I'll stay to run the guesthouse with you.

495
00:34:12,949 --> 00:34:14,190
Do you want to drink

496
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:15,770
or go fishing?

497
00:34:16,330 --> 00:34:17,530
Let's do it together.

498
00:34:26,580 --> 00:34:27,179
Come on,

499
00:34:27,409 --> 00:34:28,110
everyone.

500
00:34:28,300 --> 00:34:28,900
Okay.

501
00:34:29,790 --> 00:34:31,350
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

502
00:34:35,690 --> 00:34:37,489
People say that when you get old,

503
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:40,179
you become more and more like a child.

504
00:34:40,570 --> 00:34:41,940
Your son has grown up.

505
00:34:42,260 --> 00:34:43,659
Stop acting like a child.

506
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:45,929
Who's old, uncle?

507
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:47,650
Uncle? Me?

508
00:34:47,730 --> 00:34:49,170
You look like my uncle, you know?

509
00:34:49,170 --> 00:34:50,570
I'm your grandma!

510
00:34:51,330 --> 00:34:52,239
You're a doctor.

511
00:34:52,239 --> 00:34:53,370
Why don't you get
aesthetic treatments yourself?

512
00:34:53,370 --> 00:34:54,350
How dare you say I'm old?

513
00:34:54,350 --> 00:34:54,790
I...

514
00:34:54,820 --> 00:34:56,020
I look older than you?

515
00:34:56,710 --> 00:34:58,640
Should we buy a mirror for your dad?

516
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:08,360
Your dad looks really happy.

517
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:13,520
When I'm with you,

518
00:35:13,740 --> 00:35:14,910
I'm also happy.

519
00:35:18,970 --> 00:35:20,230
How do I work my glutes?

520
00:35:20,660 --> 00:35:22,230
Raise your butt, like this.

521
00:35:22,230 --> 00:35:24,530
How? Stand up and show me.

522
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:26,470
Just raise your butt.

523
00:35:26,470 --> 00:35:27,600
It's easy,

524
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:28,540
right?

525
00:35:29,570 --> 00:35:30,410
Right?

526
00:35:30,410 --> 00:35:31,240
Are you doing it right?

527
00:35:31,240 --> 00:35:32,080
Yes.

528
00:35:33,810 --> 00:35:34,440
Uncle Hua,

529
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,040
when you practice squats...

530
00:35:37,650 --> 00:35:38,510
It's like this.

531
00:35:38,510 --> 00:35:39,580
Come on.

532
00:35:39,650 --> 00:35:40,180
Your turn.

533
00:35:40,180 --> 00:35:41,420
No need. My glutes are strong.

534
00:35:41,420 --> 00:35:41,880
Really?

535
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:43,190
Very strong.

536
00:35:43,190 --> 00:35:44,090
Looks good.

537
00:35:44,090 --> 00:35:44,850
You should squat.

538
00:35:44,850 --> 00:35:45,790
You almost hit your head.

539
00:35:45,790 --> 00:35:46,420
Dudu,

540
00:35:46,420 --> 00:35:47,860
watch him squat for 10 minutes.

541
00:35:47,860 --> 00:35:50,390
The wish has never really
changed the world.

542
00:35:51,060 --> 00:35:52,830
It made us travel a long way,

543
00:35:53,830 --> 00:35:54,900
only to

544
00:35:55,300 --> 00:35:57,370
bring us right back to each other.
